{
  "texts": [
    "Quite amazingly, the ancient tradition of stealing kills from hungry lions in East Africa by the Dorobo tribe was recently recorded by the BBC EARTH field team, available freely on YouTube (See \"Grasslands: Stealing meat from the mouth of lions Human Planet\").",
    "Even today, humans retain many features of aposematic animals, from individual behavior to the behavior of various human groups, and even nation states, where aposematic (warning, threatening) tactics play a major, sometimes a leading, role in international politics.",
    "Jordania 10.3389/fpsyg.2023.1271854 Frontiers in Psychology 11 frontiersin.org",
    "The aposematic nature of humans is a powerful legacy of our evolutionary history, and its serious study might become one of the promising directions of research of evolutionary biology and evolutionary psychology."
  ]
}